gh parts of the walls, giving it an aura of reverence. There are several red mats (probably for meditating) that seem to be arranged equal distance from each other. There are also two lines where the mats had been pushed aside and trodden upon. These lines emanate from two doors, one on the left side of the room and one on the right. In between the doors is another mosaic, this one purely of a sun. Trickling down the walls is an excess of blood. Some of it looks dried and old, but other parts look to be still running. At once, you feel uncomfortable and things look a little bit more twisted than previously. <br>
<br>
