As Serin studies the walls from a distance, it seems as if there are bits of skin embedded in the stone... there looks to be some sort of white dust over it as well, but his distance prevents him from identifying it. Gheant ventures a guess that it was goblins, however this seems totally off the mark. <br>
As Serin takes in his surroundings, he deducts that there is some kind of a blast radius, since the blood is splattered on only certain sides of the pillars. It looks like the center of the blast was between the two pillars nearest the two doors. ::two hidden checks::<br>
While Serin is pondering all of this, Gheant shuffles his feet and looks around at the masonry of the building. While studying the floor he notices some scuff marks... He isn't readily able to identify them however, as a dwarven fighter doesn't know much about tracks... <p>-----------------<br>
